        "status": "risk",
        "issue": "Batch of 10 messages at ~3s each = up to 30s sequential processing, which equals or exceeds the 30s visibility timeout. Messages near the end of a batch will become visible again mid-processing, causing duplicate processing. No idempotency mechanism mentioned."
      },
      {
        "from": "SQS Queue",
        "to": "Dead-Letter Queue",
        "status": "broken",
        "issue": "No DLQ configured. Poison messages (corrupt images, unsupported formats, oversized files) will retry infinitely, consuming worker capacity that is already critically insufficient."
      }
    ],
    "contract_compliance": "Cannot assess — no schema or contract definition provided for job messages. Unknown whether malformed messages are validated or rejected.",
    "data_flow_integrity": "At risk. Duplicate processing is near-certain under load due to visibility timeout races. Without idempotency keys or deduplication, the same image may be processed and stored multiple times, leading to data corruption or inflated storage costs."
  },

  "observability_review": {
    "logging": {
      "coverage": "gaps",
      "gaps": [
        "No logging of queue depth or backlog size — operators cannot see the queue growing",
        "No logging of per-job processing duration — cannot identify slow jobs",
        "No logging of message receive count (ApproximateReceiveCount) — cannot detect poison messages",
        "No logging of visibility timeout breaches — duplicate processing is silent",
        "No correlation ID or trace ID across the job lifecycle"
      ]
    },
    "metrics": {
      "coverage": "Two counters (jobs_processed_total, jobs_failed_total) are a start but critically incomplete for production",
      "gaps": [
        "CRITICAL: No queue depth metric (ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible) — the primary signal for the capacity problem is invisible",
        "CRITICAL: No queue age metric (ApproximateAgeOfOldestMessage) — cannot detect growing latency",
        "No job_processing_duration_seconds histogram — cannot detect slowdowns or timeout risks",
        "No jobs_in_flight gauge — cannot correlate worker saturation",
        "No jobs_duplicate_total counter — duplicate processing from visibility timeout races is invisible",
        "No error breakdown by type (transient vs permanent failure)",
        "No SQS API error metrics (ReceiveMessage failures, DeleteMessage failures)"
      ]
    },
    "tracing": {
      "coverage": "No distributed tracing mentioned",
      "gaps": [
        "No trace context propagation from job producer to worker",
        "Cannot trace an image through the full pipeline (upload → queue → process → store)"
      ]
    },
    "debugging_capability": "Poor. At 3am, an on-call engineer would see jobs_processed_total flatline and jobs_failed_total spike, but would have no visibility into WHY: no queue depth, no processing latency, no error categorization, no poison message detection. They would be flying blind."
